---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Pitch & Contact"
	description="How to pitch Letters from the Floor — essays, reported pieces, and profiles within our beat."
>
	<h1>Pitch &amp; Contact</h1>

	<p>
		We accept pitches for essays, reported pieces, and profiles within our beat (see <a href="/about"
			>About</a
		>). We do not currently pay for freelance work, though we hope to in time.
	</p>

	<p>A good pitch includes:</p>

	<ol>
		<li>A working title or angle</li>
		<li>Two or three sentences on what the piece would argue or report</li>
		<li>Why now, why us</li>
		<li>Your relevant experience or sources</li>
	</ol>

	<p>
		Send to: <a href="mailto:pitches@lettersfromthefloor.com">pitches@lettersfromthefloor.com</a>
	</p>

	<p>
		We respond to most pitches within two weeks. Please don't follow up before then unless
		something material has changed.
	</p>

	<p>
		For tips, leads, or stories you'd like us to look into:
		<a href="mailto:tips@lettersfromthefloor.com">tips@lettersfromthefloor.com</a>
	</p>

	<p>
		For press inquiries:
		<a href="mailto:press@lettersfromthefloor.com">press@lettersfromthefloor.com</a>
	</p>
</BaseLayout>
